      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T13:06:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we make the backing pool fixed-size, can we also make the per-thread cache fixed-size and inline here instead of using a `u32 *` vector?\n\nSomething like an inline index array plus `len` would avoid pointer chasing and any vector allocation/reallocation in the fast path. Refill/drain would then just copy bounded batches under the backing-pool lock.",
      "revId": "70a24193ddf72811791adf2988e1975431acf9b1",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e6d2bf97_49b0f9e5",
        "filename": "src/vlib/pool_cache.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 176,
      "author": {
        "id": 361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T13:06:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we should make this a fixed-size primitive instead of allowing refill to grow the backing pool. `pool_get_aligned()` can reallocate `_pool`, but other workers may already hold element pointers returned by `*_pool_cache_elt_at_index()`. The spinlock only protects the refill/drain operation, not those external users, so growth can invalidate live pointers.\n\nA simpler contract would be: callers preallocate/init a fixed capacity up front, workers only move indices between the fixed backing pool and per-thread caches, and allocation fails/asserts when capacity is exhausted.",
      "revId": "70a24193ddf72811791adf2988e1975431acf9b1",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "44b42ebe_d6adfe78",
        "filename": "src/vlib/pool_cache.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 233,
      "author": {
        "id": 361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T13:06:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Same semantic issue as iteration: after `*_pool_cache_free()` pushes an index into a per-thread cache, `pool_is_free_index()` still reports it as allocated in the backing pool. Exposing this as `*_pool_cache_is_free_index()` is likely to mislead callers expecting normal pool semantics.",
      "revId": "70a24193ddf72811791adf2988e1975431acf9b1",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "277b34dc_c5450625",
        "filename": "src/vlib/pool_cache.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 288,
      "author": {
        "id": 361
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T13:06:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This exposes normal pool iteration semantics, but indices sitting in per-thread caches are still marked allocated in the backing pool. That means `vlib_pool_cache_foreach()` will visit objects that have already been returned to the cache.\n\nIf the cache remains separate from the pool free bitmap, I think we should either remove this helper or make its semantics explicit and safe for cached-free entries.",
      "revId": "70a24193ddf72811791adf2988e1975431acf9b1",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
